CAST5js implements cast5 in javascript as defined in RFC 2144. CAST5 is a common OpenPGP cipher.

Porting http://golang.org/src/pkg/crypto/cast5/cast5.go (only good example I could find) to javascript for use with Dr. Hanewinkel's http://www.hanewin.net/encrypt/ openPGP javascript suite.


// 16 byte key
var key = '0123456789abcdef';

// construct js object
var c = new cast5(key);


var plainText = "I love Ramona!";

var cryptText = c.encrypt(plainText);

var verifyPlain = c.decrypt(cryptText);

if ( verifyPlain === plainText ) {
	alert("CAST5js - Test Passed.");
} else {
	alert("CAST5js - Test Failed.");
}